{
  "stem": "19111.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, it was absolutely wonderful.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were very loving and wonderful people.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I remember most of the priests made a special effort to wave to us and say hello, and ask how we are.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "One in particular, he was-- his name was [NON-ENGLISH] David.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He was-- name was Father David.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he wore these long black robes, you know, and-- and the special hats.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He befriended us so much that at times, mother invited him to come Sunday for tea and biscuits.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he would come with his long robe.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I-- I would sit on his lap and he would-- he would actually hug me and tell me how much he loves me.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And so that the next morning before I woke up to go to school, he would throw this apples and pears, and-- and-- and flowers, into the-- up the second floor, right through-- through the windows.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And [SIGHS] he really cared for us very much.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the relationship did not change.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But the circumstances have changed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I'll tell you a little bit more about it as we go on.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I heard-- my father used to listen to the news when-- 1939 when the Germans attacked Poland, the war broke out in 1939.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they ran a-- actually, I should say that before the war broke out, Hitler and Stalin had an agreement, just about a week before.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they agreed that when the Germans will run over Poland, that part of it is going to be taken over by Russia.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And as it turned out, that Vilna, and Bialostocka, and some of the eastern part of Poland was designated as a part that the Russians would take over.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
